Endpoint Method Description Auth Required Notes <code>/account/register</code> <code>POST</code> Register a new user account ❌ No Terms of service must be accepted <p>URL Example: <pre><code>POST https://instance.tld/api/account/register
</code></pre></p> <p>Request Body: <pre><code>{
  "username": "string", // Mandatory
  "displayName": "string", // Mandatory
  "password": "string", // Mandatory
  "tos": true // Mandatory
}
</code></pre></p> <p>Response Example: <pre><code>{
  "success": true,
  "data": {
    "message": "Account created successfully",
    "userId": "user-123",
    "identity": "@username@instance.tld"
  }
}
</code></pre></p>

Endpoint Method Description Auth Required Notes <code>/account/login</code> <code>POST</code> Authenticate user and obtain session token ❌ No Username format: @username@instance.tld <p>URL Example: <pre><code>POST https://instance.tld/api/account/login
</code></pre></p> <p>Request Body: <pre><code>{
  "identity": "@username@instance.tld", // Mandatory
  "password": "string" // Mandatory
}
</code></pre></p> <p>Response Example: <pre><code>{
  "success": true,
  "data": {
    "token": "session-token-here",
    "identity": "@username@instance.tld",
    "expiresAt": "2025-08-10T12:00:00Z"
  }
}
</code></pre></p> <p>This token must be provided in the <code>Authorization</code> header as a Bearer token on endpoints that require authentication. Store this token in a safe place.</p>

Endpoint Method Description Auth Required Notes <code>/account/me</code> <code>PUT</code> Update user account information ✅ Yes Only updates fields provided in the request body <p>URL Example: <pre><code>PUT https://instance.tld/api/account/me
</code></pre></p> <p>Request Body: <pre><code>{
  "displayName": "string", // Optional
  "password": "string" // Optional
}
</code></pre></p> <p>Response Example: <pre><code>{
  "success": true,
  "data": {
    "message": "Account information updated successfully"
  }
}
</code></pre></p>

Endpoint Method Description Auth Required Notes <code>/account/me</code> <code>GET</code> Get authenticated user account information ✅ Yes Returns identity in @username@instance.tld format <p>URL Example: <pre><code>GET https://instance.tld/api/account/me
</code></pre></p> <p>Response Example: <pre><code>{
  "success": true,
  "data": {
    "identity": "@username@instance.tld",
    "displayName": "User Display Name",
    "accountCreated": "2025-01-01T00:00:00Z",
    "isVerified": true
  }
}
</code></pre></p>

Endpoint Method Description Auth Required Notes <code>/account/logout</code> <code>POST</code> Log out authenticated user ✅ Yes Invalidates session token <p>URL Example: <pre><code>POST https://instance.tld/api/account/logout
</code></pre></p> <p>Response Example: <pre><code>{
  "success": true,
  "data": {
    "message": "Successfully logged out"
  }
}
</code></pre></p>

Endpoint Method Description Auth Required Notes <code>/account/me</code> <code>DELETE</code> Delete user account ✅ Yes Permanent account deletion <p>URL Example: <pre><code>DELETE https://instance.tld/api/account/me
</code></pre></p> <p>Request Body: <pre><code>{
  "password": "string" // Mandatory
}
</code></pre></p> <p>Response Example: <pre><code>{
  "success": true,
  "data": {
    "message": "Account deleted successfully"
  }
}
</code></pre></p> <p>Warning</p> <p>Account deletion is permanent and irreversible. All associated data will be lost.</p>

Endpoint Method Description Auth Required Notes <code>/conversations/create/dm/:identity</code> <code>POST</code> Create a direct message conversation ✅ Yes Identity format: @username@instance.tld <p>URL Example: <pre><code>POST https://instance.tld/api/conversations/create/dm/@user@instance.tld
</code></pre></p> <p>URL Parameters: - <code>identity</code> (required) - Identity of the user with whom to create the conversation</p> <p>Response Example: <pre><code>{
  "success": true,
  "data": {
    "conversationId": "123e4567-e89b-12d3-a456-426614174000",
    "type": "dm",
    "participants": [
      "@user1@instance.tld",
      "@user2@instance.tld"
    ],
    "createdAt": "2025-08-09T12:00:00Z"
  }
}
</code></pre></p>

Endpoint Method Description Auth Required Notes <code>/conversations</code> <code>GET</code> Get list of conversations ✅ Yes Returns list of conversation IDs <p>URL Example: <pre><code>GET https://instance.tld/api/conversations
</code></pre></p> <p>Response Example: <pre><code>{
  "success": true,
  "data": {
    "conversations": [
      {
        "conversationId": "123e4567-e89b-12d3-a456-426614174000",
        "type": "dm",
        "participants": ["@user1@instance.tld", "@user2@instance.tld"],
        "lastActivity": "2025-08-09T11:30:00Z"
      },
      {
        "conversationId": "123e4567-e89b-12d3-a456-426614174000",
        "type": "group",
        "name": "My Group",
        "memberCount": 5,
        "lastActivity": "2025-08-09T10:15:00Z"
      }
    ]
  }
}
</code></pre></p>

Endpoint Method Description Auth Required Notes <code>/conversations/leave/:conversationId</code> <code>POST</code> Leave a conversation ✅ Yes Leaves the specified conversation <p>URL Example: <pre><code>POST https://instance.tld/api/conversations/leave/123e4567-e89b-12d3-a456-426614174000
</code></pre></p> <p>URL Parameters: - <code>conversationId</code> (required) - ID of the conversation to leave</p> <p>Response Example: <pre><code>{
  "success": true,
  "data": {
    "message": "Successfully left conversation",
    "conversationId": "123e4567-e89b-12d3-a456-426614174000"
  }
}
</code></pre></p> <p>Info</p> <ul> <li>For group conversations, leaving removes you from the member list</li> <li>For direct messages, this hides the conversation from your list</li> <li>If you are the last member of a group, the conversation will be deleted</li> </ul>

Endpoint Method Description Auth Required Notes <code>/messages/send/:conversationId</code> <code>POST</code> Send a message in a conversation ✅ Yes Sends a message to the specified conversation <p>URL Example: <pre><code>POST https://instance.tld/api/messages/send/conv-123
</code></pre></p> <p>URL Parameters: - <code>conversationId</code> (required) - Conversation ID</p> <p>Request Body: <pre><code>{
  "content": "Hello, how are you?"
}
</code></pre></p> <p>Required Parameters: - <code>content</code> (required) - Message content</p> <p>Response Example: <pre><code>{
  "success": true,
  "messageId": "msg-789",
  "conversationId": "conv-123",
  "content": "Hello, how are you?",
  "author": "@username@instance.tld",
  "timestamp": "2025-08-09T12:00:00Z"
}
</code></pre></p>
